          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1625593536669-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a baking tray with the <strong>harissa paste, </strong>a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min or until the butternut squash is beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, deseed the<strong> red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p><p>Cut the<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1625593575524-x200.jpg",
